org.apache.drill.jdbc.test

Class Drill2489CallsAfterCloseThrowExceptionsTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.drill.test.BaseTest
      • org.apache.drill.test.DrillTest
        • org.apache.drill.exec.ExecTest
          • org.apache.drill.jdbc.JdbcTestBase
            • org.apache.drill.jdbc.test.Drill2489CallsAfterCloseThrowExceptionsTest

  • public class Drill2489CallsAfterCloseThrowExceptionsTest
extends JdbcTestBase
    Test class for JDBC requirement that almost all methods throw SQLException when called on a closed primary object (e.g., Connection, ResultSet, etc.).

    NOTE: This test currently covers: Connection, Statement, PreparedStatement, ResultSet, ResultSetMetaData, and DatabaseMetaData.

    It does not cover unimplemented CallableStatement or any relevant secondary objects such as Array or Struct).
